sentences: Isaiah Rivera (born March 20, 1997), professionally known as Wifisfuneral, is an American rapper.
He is best known for his breakthrough mixtapes Black Heart Revenge, When Hell Falls, Ethernet and Boy Who Cried Wolf.
He is signed to Alamo Records and Empire Records and was previously signed to Interscope Records.
In early 2020, Wifisfuneral announced his retirement; however, this proved to be short-lived as he released his debut album, Pain?, in that year.

Isaih Rivera was born on March 20, 1997, in the Bronx borough of New York City, to a Puerto Rican mother and a Jamaican father.
His biological father, who was a freestyle battle rapper in The Bronx, left the family when Rivera was only three years old.
Rivera's interest in hip-hop began when he first watched The Notorious B.I.G.. tribute "Mo Money Mo Problems" music video with Puff Daddy and Ma$e.
